Personnel expenses, excluding stock-based compensation, increased 6% in 2022 compared to 2021, due to an increase in
salary expense of $139 million and an increase in bonus expense accruals of $66 million, partially offset by the $136 million
expense, recorded in 2021, associated with the return of government assistance received through various government aid programs.
Employee headcount of approximately 21,600 as of December 31, 2022 increased by 6% as compared to December 31, 2021.
Personnel expenses in 2022 and employee headcount as of December 31, 2022 were reduced due to the transfer of certain customer
service operations of Booking.com to Majorel which shifted costs from personnel expenses to sales and other expenses. Stock-
based compensation expense was $404 million in 2022 compared to $370 million in 2021.
